ctions run smoothly.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. How does the Treasurer collaborate with the auditor and Executive Director in the review and presentation of annual audited financial statements?\n2. What specific responsibilities does the Secretary have in terms of maintaining and passing on organizational files and records?\n3. What role does the Treasurer play in ensuring that complete and accurate financial records are kept in accordance with generally accepted accounting practices?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "06f917c2-6a88-4ba8-81c5-67cc361ae906", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "8", "file_name": "COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 693818, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "c3814c303850a5fdd8d623ab085623ff0c9895db4c7109c42e3a2139c6786ae0", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "4280fed7-a776-4833-b49f-97b46bdb6f4e", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "8", "file_name": "COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 693818, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "c6a1eb1508f9d09b1b55361ccbf5f6595924225fcd711c4473d7b175ff31be23", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "maintenance of, the files and records of the organization to be passed \non to future officers and ensure the security and confidentiality of all such files and records.\nTreasurer\nEnsures that the Board receives relevant and regular financial statements. \nEnsures that an annual financial budget is done. \nRecommends a competent auditor to be appointed annually.\nCollaborates with the auditor and Executive Director in the review and presentation of annual \naudited financial statements.\nEnsures that complete and accurate financial records are kept in accordance with generally \naccepted accounting practices.\nActs as a signing authority for the organization as approved in the By-laws or by a Board \nresolution.\n\u2022\n\u2022\n\u2022\n\u2022\n\u2022\n\u2022\n\u2022\n\u2022\nBOARD OFFICER \nSAMPLE \nDESCRIPTION\n\u2022\n\u2022\n\u2022\n\u2022\n\u2022\n\u2022\n\u2022\n\u2022\n\u2022", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1508, "end_char_idx": 2289, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "cbf0c62c-94f0-4563-abcc-0f8f58d58d89": {"__data__": {"id_": "cbf0c62c-94f0-4563-abcc-0f8f58d58d89", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "9", "file_name": "COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 693818, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "This section outlines the responsibilities of the Secretary and Treasurer on the Board of Directors. The Secretary is responsible for maintaining and passing on organizational files and records, while the Treasurer ensures the Board receives financial statements, oversees the annual budget, and works with auditors to review financial statements. Both officers play crucial roles in ensuring the organization's financial and administrative functions run smoothly.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses the collective responsibility of the board of directors in governing a nonprofit corporation. It emphasizes the importance of decisions being made collectively by the board, with no individual board member having the authority to act on behalf of the organization without board authorization. Board members are expected to honor all decisions made by the board, and any dissent should be recorded in the minutes. Confidentiality is also highlighted as essential for maintaining trust within the organization among the board, director, staff, and members.", "section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the importance of board members making decisions with the long-term health of the organization in mind, the collective responsibility of the board in making decisions, and the need for board members to honor decisions made collectively by the board. The entities mentioned in the section are board members, the executive director, and the organization as a whole.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. How does the Board of Directors ensure that decisions are made collectively and in the best interest of the organization's long-term health?\n2. What are the specific responsibilities and limitations of individual board members, including the Secretary and Treasurer, in terms of decision-making and authority within the organization?\n3. How does the organization handle dissent among board members regarding decisions made collectively by the board, and what policies are in place to address this issue?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "a3bba9d6-593a-49db-8316-467f8d20423b", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "9", "file_name": "COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 693818, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "71c86081fb1849a470dd54c31d177b67a4e2e35d1d9e83065ad061b15b82bc78", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "66b929a5-82fa-45b3-88d0-dc09f35b9d87", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "772ee050d27f2fb27b59e2d03ab4867fbaef9038c61cf11bfe91527bab8f4631", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "9\nBOARD FUNDAMENTALS\n1.  \u201cWearing one hat\u201d only\nAlthough the board benefits from the expertise and perspectives that individuals holding various \nresponsibilities may have, (e.g. executive director, staff \u2018reps\u2019, program volunteers etc.), it is important \nthat all board members, regardless of their positions , make decisions with the long-term health of \nthe organization  in mind and not with their interest in mind.Secretary\n2.  Board decisions can only be made \u2018around the table\u2019\nGovernance of the nonprofit corporation is a collective board responsibility. No individual trustee/\nboard member, not even the president, can make decisions or act in the name of the organization \nunless having been authorized to do so by board resolution. A board member may choose to carry \nout non-board volunteer tasks but does so under the authority of the executive director. \n3.  Honoring Decisions\nBoard members must honor all decisions made collectively by the board. Speaking against decisions \nmade by board members needs to be dealt with immediately (and merits a board discussion and \npolicy). Any board member who", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 1113, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "66b929a5-82fa-45b3-88d0-dc09f35b9d87": {"__data__": {"id_": "66b929a5-82fa-45b3-88d0-dc09f35b9d87", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "9", "file_name": "COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 693818, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the importance of board members making decisions with the long-term health of the organization in mind, the collective responsibility of the board in making decisions, and the need for board members to honor decisions made collectively by the board. The entities mentioned in the section are board members, the executive director, and the organization as a whole.", "next_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include speaking against board decisions, confidentiality, and maintaining trust within the organization. Entities mentioned include board members, directors, staff, and members. The section emphasizes the importance of addressing dissent within the board, maintaining confidentiality of board meetings, and handling sensitive issues with care.", "section_summary": "This section discusses the collective responsibility of the board of directors in governing a nonprofit corporation. It emphasizes the importance of decisions being made collectively by the board, with no individual board member having the authority to act on behalf of the organization without board authorization. Board members are expected to honor all decisions made by the board, and any dissent should be recorded in the minutes. Confidentiality is also highlighted as essential for maintaining trust within the organization among the board, director, staff, and members.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. How does this document outline the collective responsibility of the board of directors in governing a nonprofit corporation?\n2. What steps should board members take if they do not support a particular board decision or believe it may lead to mismanagement or conflict of interest?\n3. Why is confidentiality emphasized as essential for maintaining trust within the organizatio