e collectively by the board. Speaking against decisions \nmade by board members needs to be dealt with immediately (and merits a board discussion and \npolicy). Any board member who does not support a particular board decision or who feels that the \ndecision made is grounds for mismanagement or conflict of interest can ask to have their dissent \nrecorded in the minutes. However, if after democratic debate a board member cannot support and \nhonor the decision, s/he should resign.\n4.  Confidentiality\nIn order to maintain a strong level of trust at all levels of the organization  - board, director, staff and \nmembers \u2013 it is essential that all particulars of", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 458, "end_char_idx": 1595, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "436e63f4-0015-4d01-a96f-b17b713f1b43": {"__data__": {"id_": "436e63f4-0015-4d01-a96f-b17b713f1b43", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "9", "file_name": "COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 693818, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "This section discusses the collective responsibility of the board of directors in governing a nonprofit corporation. It emphasizes the importance of decisions being made collectively by the board, with no individual board member having the authority to act on behalf of the organization without board authorization. Board members are expected to honor all decisions made by the board, and any dissent should be recorded in the minutes. Confidentiality is also highlighted as essential for maintaining trust within the organization among the board, director, staff, and members.", "next_section_summary": "The section discusses the importance of maintaining a strong level of trust within the organization, particularly among the board, director, staff, and members. It emphasizes the need for confidentiality regarding the specifics of board meetings, especially sensitive issues such as human resources matters. The section highlights the importance of transparency in decision-making while also maintaining confidentiality to uphold trust within the organization.", "section_summary": "The key topics of this section include speaking against board decisions, confidentiality, and maintaining trust within the organization. Entities mentioned include board members, directors, staff, and members. The section emphasizes the importance of addressing dissent within the board, maintaining confidentiality of board meetings, and handling sensitive issues with care.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. How should dissent against board decisions be handled within a nonprofit organization, according to the guidelines outlined in this document?\n2. What specific measures are recommended for maintaining confidentiality within a nonprofit organization, particularly in relation to sensitive issues like human resources matters?\n3. What actions are suggested for board members who are unable to support or honor a decision made by the board, as outlined in this document on governance practices for nonprofit corporations?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "a3bba9d6-593a-49db-8316-467f8d20423b", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "9", "file_name": "COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 693818, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "71c86081fb1849a470dd54c31d177b67a4e2e35d1d9e83065ad061b15b82bc78", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "66b929a5-82fa-45b3-88d0-dc09f35b9d87", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "9", "file_name": "COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 693818, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "94cf3973ea82c8367b5c338e7d4f914a128c85461ef3182966758db016722696", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "755afb9a-17db-4e72-a0e3-5f796834c51f", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "53c0111dca293d91ca9cd7bc8a697f61963fa8a79761b9978171a8af59900a9a", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "Speaking against decisions \nmade by board members needs to be dealt with immediately (and merits a board discussion and \npolicy). Any board member who does not support a particular board decision or who feels that the \ndecision made is grounds for mismanagement or conflict of interest can ask to have their dissent \nrecorded in the minutes. However, if after democratic debate a board member cannot support and \nhonor the decision, s/he should resign.\n4.  Confidentiality\nIn order to maintain a strong level of trust at all levels of the organization  - board, director, staff and \nmembers \u2013 it is essential that all particulars of a Board meeting are not discussed with others outside \nthe meetings. While the minutes of all board meetings need to be made available to members and \nboard members need to be able to explain the reasons for the decisions, the specifics of the meeting \nshould not be discussed. Neither in the minutes nor in outside discussions should \u201cwho said what \nto whom\u201d be discussed. In the case of sensitive issues (e.g. human resources \u2013 hiring, firing, salaries \nand evaluation) it is extremely important", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 963, "end_char_idx": 2093, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "755afb9a-17db-4e72-a0e3-5f796834c51f": {"__data__": {"id_": "755afb9a-17db-4e72-a0e3-5f796834c51f", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "9", "file_name": "COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 693818, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include speaking against board decisions, confidentiality, and maintaining trust within the organization. Entities mentioned include board members, directors, staff, and members. The section emphasizes the importance of addressing dissent within the board, maintaining confidentiality of board meetings, and handling sensitive issues with care.", "next_section_summary": "The section discusses the importance of good communication, clarity of roles and responsibilities, and being prepared for board meetings. It emphasizes the need for agendas to be prepared before meetings to outline what will be discussed and for minutes to be taken to document decisions and next steps. Tips for creating effective agendas include including estimated times for each item and assigning responsibility for agenda creation after each meeting.", "section_summary": "The section discusses the importance of maintaining a strong level of trust within the organization, particularly among the board, director, staff, and members. It emphasizes the need for confidentiality regarding the specifics of board meetings, especially sensitive issues such as human resources matters. The section highlights the importance of transparency in decision-making while also maintaining confidentiality to uphold trust within the organization.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answ