ps. Tips for creating a good agenda include including approximate times for each item, assigning the task of agenda creation to a board member or staff member, and filing minutes carefully after each meeting. It also mentions the traditional role of the secretary in taking minutes, but suggests rotating minute takers. Additionally, it suggests putting easy and important items first on the agenda to ensure they are addressed even if not all topics are discussed.", "next_section_summary": "This section provides guidance on organizing board meetings effectively, emphasizing the importance of prioritizing key items on the agenda and ensuring that important resolutions are not rushed through. It also lists common items found on board meeting agendas, such as the organization name, meeting date, attendance, quorum, approval of minutes, agenda approval, and meeting facilitation. The section highlights the basics of conducting a board meeting efficiently and effectively.", "section_summary": "This section provides guidance on creating agendas and taking minutes for board meetings. It emphasizes the importance of clear communication about who will create the agenda for each meeting and the value of filing minutes carefully for future reference. The traditional role of the secretary in taking minutes is mentioned, but rotating minute takers is also suggested. It is recommended to prioritize important items on the agenda to ensure they are addressed before the meeting ends. Common items found on board meeting agendas are listed, including the organization name, meeting date, attendance, quorum, approval of minutes, and discussion of key topics.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. How can organizations ensure that important resolutions are not rushed through during board meetings?\n2. What are some common items that are typically found on board meeting agendas?\n3. What are some tips for creating a good agenda for board meetings, according to the provided context?"}, "ex