ve anything else to add?", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 831, "end_char_idx": 1847, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "87356b08-dfb4-472a-8edc-734271dfce41": {"__data__": {"id_": "87356b08-dfb4-472a-8edc-734271dfce41", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "22", "file_name": "COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\COCo-BoardOfDirectors-3-1.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 693818, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the responsibilities and characteristics of an effective board of directors. This includes monitoring financial performance, supporting fundraising efforts, being open to different perspectives, having a diverse range of expertise, engaging members more fully, considering the organization's role in shaping public policy, and ensuring compliance with corporate, labour, and tax requirements. The section also prompts board members to reflect on their contributions to the organization and to provide feedback or suggestions for improvement.", "next_section_summary": "This section provides a list of key resources for non-profit organizations to have at their fingertips. The resources include links to websites such as the Human Resources Council, Board Cafe, Commission des normes du travail, Revenue Canada, and Revenu Qu\u00e9bec. Additionally, there are links to tools and publications related to governance, finance, and human resources. The section aims to provide valuable resources for non-profit organizations to access important information and support.", "section_summary": "This section provides a list of key resources for nonprofit organizations and their board of directors. It includes links to COCo's toolbox and publications, a guide for nonprofit board members by P